A sports car driver who had broken down has died after a tipper lorry collided with his vehicle as it stood stricken on the side of the road.

The 44-year-old's MGB vehicle had stopped at the side of the A2 in Kent when a Scania tipper lorry hit it, police said today.

The middle-aged man, who has not yet been named, was declared dead at the scene.

Tragic: A middle aged man died after his broken down sports car was crushed by a lorry on the hard shoulder of a dual carriageway

Scene: Officers survey the fatal crash which happened on the London-bound A2 in Kent

The lorry driver was unhurt but was treated for shock following the collision on the London-bound carriageway of the A2 between Dover and Canterbury yesterday.

The road was closed for almost five hours following the collision as emergency services dealt with the incident and the vehicles were removed from the roadside.

Kent Police today appealed for witnesses to come forward.

